Change-Id: I2b70cd065d2bad9632e68b2d6d7aaa4287a1dc46","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/8d72537c6abf5a44103b57b9c2e22c14f5f49698"},{"sha":"33bbc5886f98937ee085d637628d2bfc3413c9df","author":{"name":"Taehee Jeong","email":"9658aeb0d6dabc12b71efd5872bbf9f3c41b726b@google.com"},"message":"Change QuantScaleFactor op to match constant pattern, and QuantRescale op to handle zero point correctly.

Since std.constant -> tfr.constant_tensor pattern is canonicalized to tf.Const -> tfr.cast, QuantScaleFactor should look for the latter pattern.

For the zero point input in QuantRescale op, it is being passed as a i64 scalar. Fot it to be used in tf ops, it should be converted to tensor first.

[{"sha":"2433281f9a1d7a093d3d3a553d844a7696f3e82a","author":{"name":"mergify[bot]","email":"b09a6ee808b67e98a221404e7aaa52e0398a4954@users.noreply.github.com"},"message":"chore(*) separate proxy template resolvers (#2394) (#2424)

Breaking the dependency between the simple proxy template resolver and
the default fallback lets us specify the fallback as a default proxy
template resolver. This in turn, makes it possible for plugins to wrap
the default resolver so that this can be extended.

Moving the default ProxyTemplate resources out of pkg/xds/template
breaks a circular dependency between this package and xds/generator.

Signed-off-by: James Peach <james.peach@konghq.com>
(cherry picked from commit 6b6f3c110e75cf918e5e05f329cc90c56e05ce37)

Co-authored-by: James Peach <james.peach@konghq.com>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kumahq/kuma/commits/2433281f9a1d7a093d3d3a553d844a7696f3e82a"}]
